{"parentUuid":"e7bd921a-60e6-4468-b59f-f8f772245df6","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/ryan/formal-conjectures","sessionId":"8dc81e22-efbd-4a18-b20b-896c31eec768","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"ai-erdos-7","agentId":"aed3e15a5c134a6e7","slug":"woolly-discovering-hearth","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TAcNc7Qq3yQMoo6Dic8A3d","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/-\n     2→Copyright 2026 The Formal Conjectures Authors.\n     3→\n     4→Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→\n     8→    https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→\n    10→Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→limitations under the License.\n    15→-/\n    16→\n    17→import FormalConjectures.Util.ProblemImports\n    18→\n    19→/-!\n    20→# Erdős Problem 146\n    21→\n    22→Erdős and Simonovits conjectured that the Turán number of any $r$-degenerate bipartite\n    23→graph $H$ satisfies $\\text{ex}(n; H) = O(n^{2 - 1/r})$.\n    24→\n    25→*Reference:* [erdosproblems.com/146](https://www.erdosproblems.com/146)\n    26→\n    27→[ErSi84] Erdős, P. and Simonovits, M., *Cube-supersaturated graphs and related\n    28→problems*, Progress in graph theory (Waterloo, Ont., 1982), Academic Press,\n    29→Toronto, ON, 1984, 203-218.\n    30→\n    31→[AKS03] Alon, N., Krivelevich, M., and Sudakov, B., *Turán numbers of bipartite\n    32→graphs and related Ramsey-type questions*, Combinatorics, Probability and\n    33→Computing 12 (2003), no. 5-6, 477-494.\n    34→-/\n    35→\n    36→open SimpleGraph\n    37→\n    38→namespace Erdos146\n    39→\n    40→/-- An injective graph homomorphism from $H$ to $F$; witnesses that $F$ contains a\n    41→subgraph isomorphic to $H$. -/\n    42→def ContainsSubgraph {V U : Type*} (F : SimpleGraph V) (H : SimpleGraph U) : Prop :=\n    43→  ∃ f : U → V, Function.Injective f ∧ ∀ u v : U, H.Adj u v → F.Adj (f u) (f v)\n    44→\n    45→/-- The Turán number $\\text{ex}(n; H)$: the maximum number of edges in a simple graph on $n$\n    46→vertices that contains no copy of $H$ as a subgraph. -/\n    47→noncomputable def turanNumber {U : Type*} (H : SimpleGraph U) (n : ℕ) : ℕ :=\n    48→  sSup {m : ℕ | ∃ (V : Type) (fv : Fintype V) (F : SimpleGraph V) (dr : DecidableRel F.Adj),\n    49→    haveI := fv; haveI := dr;\n    50→    Fintype.card V = n ∧ ¬ContainsSubgraph F H ∧ F.edgeFinset.card = m}\n    51→\n    52→/-- A graph $G$ is $r$-degenerate if every non-empty finite set of vertices contains\n    53→a vertex with at most $r$ neighbors within that set. Equivalently, every induced\n    54→subgraph of $G$ has minimum degree at most $r$. -/\n    55→def IsRDegenerateGraph {V : Type*} (G : SimpleGraph V) (r : ℕ) : Prop :=\n    56→  ∀ (S : Set V), S.Finite → S.Nonempty →\n    57→    ∃ v ∈ S, (G.neighborSet v ∩ S).ncard ≤ r\n    58→\n    59→/--\n    60→Erdős-Simonovits Conjecture (Problem #146) [ErSi84]:\n    61→If $H$ is a bipartite graph that is $r$-degenerate (i.e., every induced subgraph of $H$\n    62→has minimum degree at most $r$), then\n    63→$$\\text{ex}(n; H) \\ll n^{2 - 1/r}.$$\n    64→That is, there exists a constant $C > 0$ such that $\\text{ex}(n; H) \\leq C \\cdot n^{2 - 1/r}$\n    65→for all $n \\geq 1$.\n    66→\n    67→This is open even for $r = 2$. Alon, Krivelevich, and Sudakov [AKS03] proved the\n    68→weaker bound $\\text{ex}(n; H) \\ll n^{2 - 1/(4r)}$.\n    69→-/\n    70→@[category research open, AMS 5]\n    71→theorem erdos_146 :\n    72→    ∀ (r : ℕ), 1 ≤ r →\n    73→    ∀ (U : Type*) (H : SimpleGraph U) [Fintype U] [DecidableRel H.Adj],\n    74→      Nonempty (H.Coloring (Fin 2)) →\n    75→      IsRDegenerateGraph H r →\n    76→      ∃ C : ℝ, 0 < C ∧ ∀ n : ℕ, 1 ≤ n →\n    77→        (turanNumber H n : ℝ) ≤ C * (n : ℝ) ^ ((2 : ℝ) - 1 / (r : ℝ)) := by\n    78→  sorry\n    79→\n    80→end Erdos146\n    81→"}]},"uuid":"0c5b6fca-e9e4-4ec9-a6aa-858732af127f","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:46:35.090Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"e7bd921a-60e6-4468-b59f-f8f772245df6"}
{"parentUuid":"0c5b6fca-e9e4-4ec9-a6aa-858732af127f","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/ryan/formal-conjectures","sessionId":"8dc81e22-efbd-4a18-b20b-896c31eec768","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"ai-erdos-7","agentId":"aed3e15a5c134a6e7","slug":"woolly-discovering-hearth","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_0147dZTCuGR6fFUDkFb7FQqn","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Found it! Here are the results:\n\n**File Path:** `/home/ryan/formal-conjectures/FormalConjectures/ErdosProblems/146.lean`\n\n**Contents:**\n\nThe file contains the formalization of Erdős Problem 146, which concerns the Turán number conjecture by Erdős and Simonovits. \n\nKey components:\n- **Problem Statement:** Conjectures that for any r-degenerate bipartite graph H, the Turán number ex(n; H) = O(n^(2 - 1/r))\n- **Definitions:** \n  - `ContainsSubgraph`: Injective graph homomorphism witnessing subgraph containment\n  - `turanNumber`: The maximum number of edges in an n-vertex simple graph with no copy of H\n  - `IsRDegenerateGraph`: A graph is r-degenerate if every finite nonempty set of vertices contains a vertex with at most r neighbors in that set\n- **Main Theorem:** `erdos_146` formalizes the conjecture as a Lean theorem statement with the condition that H is bipartite (expressed via `Nonempty (H.Coloring (Fin 2))`) and r-degenerate, asserting there exists a constant C > 0 such that ex(n; H) ≤ C · n^(2 - 1/r)\n- **Status:** Currently marked as an open problem (`sorry` proof)"}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1730,"cache_read_input_tokens":14675,"output_tokens":348,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1730},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CYtUcTLuyMHWMmLrhqujB","type":"assistant","